Police are on the hunt for two men who brazenly walked into a Durban hospital and allegedly shot dead a patient on Friday evening. Police spokesperson Capt Nqobile Gwala said the incident took place at 6.30pm at Clairwood Hospital, a state facility in the south of Durban. “Two armed suspects entered the hospital in Clairwood and fatally shot a 47-year-old patient. He sustained a gunshot wound to the head,” said Gwala. The motive for the killing is not known at this stage and a case of murder is being investigated.